                     <p> NOTLEY (Black and White). <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename>, son of <persName>sir <forename>Robert</forename> de <surname>Aspale</surname>, kt.</persName>
                        </persName>, 
                  grants to <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> de <surname>Aspale</surname>
                        </persName> his father the manor of
                  <placeName type="manor" key="place_106019">Slamundeshey</placeName> and all that belongs to it in <placeName key="place_106048">Blake Nottele</placeName>
                  and <placeName key="place_106188">White Nottele</placeName>, co. Essex, for the term of his life. 
                  Dated at <placeName key="place_106066">Coulingge</placeName> the Monday on the morrow of the Holy Trinity, <origDate notBefore="1328-01-25" notAfter="1329-01-24">2 Ed. III</origDate>. 
                  </p>
